5:
That concludes my explanation of
the proposed labor reforms. Are
there any questions?
8:
Hmph. You can't be serious! Why
should we give the borderlanders
better working conditions? We're
already giving them WAGES, aren't
we?
9:
BUT—let's focus on the proposal
itself. The reforms would benefit the
employers as much as the
employed.
12:
Exactly. This solution stands to
enrich the lives of ALL parties
concerned.
15:
I cannot imagine why one would
reject it—unless out of spite for the
laborers.
20:
I would prefer our board's decision
to be unanimous. I would be happy
to hear and address any concerns
you have.
23:
Tch... That CHILD'S gotten full of
herself. *grumble* "Light of the
Desert"... Ha!
31:
*sigh* I knew it wouldn't be easy,
but... the benefits are so CLEAR...
34:
Unfortunately, this issue runs deeper
than the scope of one proposal.
37:
I know... They're just afraid to try
anything new. But the OLD ways are
all rooted in discrimination.
41:
So no matter how long a fight it is, I
will never—
45:
LADY SARLIHA! Someone's stolen an
arcane artifact! We've got reports
that he's holed up in the excavation
site.
50:
W-we don't know. Around half are
unaccounted for!
53: Understood. I will embark at once.
57:
Sarliha, WAIT! It's too dangerous to
rush in alone! What if it's—
60:
It IS a trap. Given the timing, I can
only imagine his true target is me.
62:
The culprit likely has the workers
held hostage. Cornering him with
guards puts innocent lives at risk.
65:
And besides... I'm not alone. YOU are
with me. Right?
68:
L-Lady Sarliha?! You really came...
Aha... Hahaha...
74:
You escaped?! Or... did someone
release you?
77:
N-none of your business! Don't try
anything funny—I've got THIS!
79:
If I activate the artifact, it'll blast
these whole ruins!
81:
Please, calm down. I will hear your
demands.
84:
I demand... I-I demand your life! It's
either you or my family!
96:
Stay back, please. I know what I'm
doing.
100:
And you... There's nothing to be
afraid of. Do what you must.
104:
I promise, I will save everyone—you
and your family included.
107:
Why?! How can you say things like
that?!
109:
Because life is precious. I do not
wish to see any lost here.
112:
Ah?! The artifact?! But I didn't do
anything!
120:
It seems the true culprit activated it
remotely. They must have planned
to sacrifice this man from the start.
124: Uh, is it safe to touch that thing?
127:
It's fine. It was a close call, but I
managed to nullify its power with
my own artifact.
131:
Tch. Then nullify the damn thing
from the start.
135:
I knew the ringleader had to be
watching from somewhere—so I
pushed them for a hint, is all.
137:
Real risky hint. But fine. They're all
yours.
142:
Let's see... A ledger, and the artifact's
activator.
145:
I had my suspicions, but I believe
these constitute concrete evidence
of your attempts on my life.
148:
Things should settle down, now that
the true culprit's been apprehended.
150:
Thank you, everyone—for all your
help.
156:
I realize now... Ever since I lost my
friend, I've been fighting something I
couldn't see.
159:
Fighting and fighting... Chasing after
shadows in the dark, with nothing
but formless ideals to guide me.
161:
And I was so... disappointed in my
lack of power.
168:
You don't have to fight alone. You
have all of us at your back.
171:
Thank you. I swear... I WILL change
the world.
174:
However long it takes... Someday.
SOMEDAY, we will prevail.
